      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="210-36L-"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">Out of</hi> H<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">ORACE</hi>.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">Written in the Year</hi> 1716.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">H</hi>OW blest is he, who for his Country dies;</l><l/><l n="2" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-2">Since Death pursue the Coward as he flies,</l><l/><l n="3" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-3">The Youth, in vain, would fly from Fate's Attack,</l><l/><l n="4" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-4">With trembling Knees, and Terror at his Back;</l><l/><l n="5" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-5">Though Fear should lend him Pinions like the wind,</l><l/><l n="6" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-6">Yet swifter Fate will seize him from behind.</l><l/><l n="7" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-7"/></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l>Virtue repuls't, yet knows not to repine;&#13;</l><l/><l n="8" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-8">But shall with unattainted Honour shine;</l><l/><l n="9" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-9">Nor stoops to take the <hi rend="underline">Staff</hi>, nor lays it down,</l><l/><l n="10" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-10">Just as the Rabble please to smile or frown.</l><l/><l n="11" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-11"/></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l>Virtue, to crown her Fav'rites, loves to try&#13;</l><l/><l n="12" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-12">Some new unbeaten Passage to the Sky;</l><l/><l n="13" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-13">Where <hi rend="underline">Jove</hi> a Seat among the Gods will give</l><l/><l n="14" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-14">To those who die, for meriting to live.</l><l/><l n="15" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-15"/></lg><lg n="4" type="stanza"><l>Next, faithful Silence hath a sure Reward:&#13;</l><l/><l n="16" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-16">Within our Breast be ev'ry Secret barr'd:</l><l/><l n="17" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-17">He who betrays his Friend, shall never be</l><l/><l n="18" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-18">Under one Roof, or in one Ship with me.</l><l/><l n="19" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-19">For, who with Traytors would his Safety trust,</l><l/><l n="20" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-20">Lest with the wicked Heaven involve the Just?</l><l/><l n="21" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-21">And, though the Villain 'scape a while, he feels</l><l/><l n="22" xml:id="spp-210-36L--line-22">Slow Vengeance, like a Blood-hound at his Heels.</l><l/><l/></lg></div>
      </div>
